export const DEMO_CONTRACT = `EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT

This Employment Agreement (the "Agreement") is made and entered into as of [Date], by and between NovaTech Solutions Inc., a Delaware corporation with its principal place of business at 1200 Innovation Drive, Wilmington, DE 19801 (the "Company"), and Alex Taylor, an individual residing at [Employee Address] (the "Employee").

WITNESSETH:

WHEREAS, the Company desires to employ the Employee as a Senior Software Engineer, and the Employee desires to accept such employment, upon the terms and conditions set forth herein.

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and promises contained herein, the parties agree as follows:

ARTICLE 1 — POSITION AND DUTIES
1.1 Title. The Employee shall serve as Senior Software Engineer, reporting to the Chief Technology Officer.
1.2 Duties. Employee shall perform all duties and responsibilities customarily associated with such position, as well as such other duties as may be reasonably assigned by the Company from time to time.
1.3 Exclusive Employment. Employee agrees to devote Employee's full business time, attention, and best efforts to the business of the Company and shall not, during the term of this Agreement, engage in any other business activity without the Company's prior written consent.

ARTICLE 2 — COMPENSATION AND BENEFITS
2.1 Base Salary. The Company shall pay Employee an annual base salary of $150,000, payable in accordance with the Company's standard payroll practices.
2.2 Bonus. Employee may be eligible for an annual performance bonus of up to 15% of base salary, as determined by the Company in its sole discretion.
2.3 Equity. Employee shall be granted 25,000 stock options under the Company's 2025 Equity Incentive Plan, which shall vest over a four-year period with a one-year cliff.
2.4 Benefits. Employee shall be entitled to participate in the Company's standard employee benefit plans, subject to the terms and conditions of those plans.

ARTICLE 3 — TERM AND TERMINATION
3.1 At-Will Employment. The employment relationship created by this Agreement is at-will and may be terminated by either party at any time, with or without cause or advance notice, subject to the notice provisions for non-renewal set forth in Article 8.
3.2 Termination Obligations. Upon termination, the Employee shall return all Company property and materials.

ARTICLE 4 — INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
4.1 Assignment of Inventions. Employee hereby assigns to the Company all right, title, and interest in and to any and all inventions, discoveries, designs, developments, improvements, software, source code, algorithms, data, documentation, creative works, and other intellectual property (collectively, "Inventions") that Employee may conceive, develop, or reduce to practice, whether alone or jointly with others, during the term of Employee's employment with the Company. This assignment applies regardless of whether such Inventions are conceived or developed on Employee's personal time, using Employee's personal equipment, or are unrelated to the Company's business, and applies to all Inventions that Employee creates during the period of employment, irrespective of the location or circumstances of creation. The sole exception shall be for Inventions that Employee can prove, through written documentation submitted to and acknowledged by the Company prior to the commencement of employment, were conceived and reduced to practice by Employee before the start date of employment and which are listed on Exhibit A attached hereto. Employee agrees to execute all documents and take all actions necessary to perfect the Company’s ownership of such Inventions.

ARTICLE 5 — NON-COMPETE COVENANT
5.1 Restrictive Covenant. During the term of employment and for a period of twenty-four (24) months following the termination of Employee's employment for any reason (whether voluntary or involuntary), Employee shall not, directly or indirectly, as an employee, consultant, owner, partner, director, officer, advisor, or in any other capacity, work for, provide services to, or have any ownership interest in any company, startup, individual, or entity that is engaged in the development, marketing, or distribution of software, technology products, digital services, or any business that competes with the Company's business, anywhere within the geographic boundaries of the United States of America. This restriction applies to all forms of employment, including but not limited to full-time employment, part-time employment, freelancing, independent contracting, and advisory roles, regardless of whether such activities are compensated. Employee acknowledges that the Company’s business is national in scope and that this restriction is reasonable and necessary to protect the Company’s legitimate business interests.

ARTICLE 6 — ARBITRATION AGREEMENT
6.1 Binding Arbitration. Any and all disputes, claims, or controversies arising out of or relating to this Agreement, Employee's employment with the Company, or the termination thereof, shall be resolved exclusively through final and binding arbitration administered by the American Arbitration Association in Wilmington, Delaware. The arbitration shall be conducted on an individual basis only. Employee expressly waives the right to bring any claim as a class, collective, or representative action, and the arbitrator shall have no authority to hear or preside over any such action. Employee further waives the right to a trial by jury for any dispute covered by this Agreement. The costs of the arbitration, including the arbitrator's fees, shall be split equally between the Company and the Employee, with each party bearing its own attorney's fees unless otherwise required by law. The decision of the arbitrator shall be final and binding, and judgment on the award may be entered in any court having jurisdiction.

ARTICLE 7 — MONITORING AND SURVEILLANCE
7.1 Consent to Monitoring. The Employee acknowledges and agrees that the Company reserves the right to monitor, intercept, review, access, and record all activity and communications occurring on or through any device that is connected to the Company's networks, systems, or infrastructure, including personally-owned mobile phones, laptops, tablets, and other electronic devices when such devices are used to access Company email, networks, or services. The Company may also monitor the contents of any personal email accounts or messaging applications that are accessed via a device connected to Company WiFi or networks. Employee expressly consents to such monitoring and acknowledges that the Company may, at its sole discretion, collect, store, and retain any data, communications, files, or logs obtained through such monitoring for an indefinite period of time, and may use such data for any business purpose, including disciplinary action, without further notice or consent. Employee waives any expectation of privacy with respect to any activity on Company networks or systems and with respect to any personal device or account accessed on Company networks.

ARTICLE 8 — AUTOMATIC RENEWAL AND NON-RENEWAL NOTICE
8.1 Term Renewal. The initial term of this Agreement shall be for a period of twelve (12) months commencing on the Effective Date (the "Initial Term"). Upon expiration of the Initial Term and each successive twelve-month term thereafter, this Agreement shall automatically renew for an additional twelve (12) month period (each a "Renewal Term") unless either party provides the other with written notice of non-renewal at least ninety (90) calendar days prior to the expiration of the then-current term. If a party fails to provide timely written notice as set forth herein, this Agreement shall automatically renew, and the Employee shall remain bound by all terms and conditions of this Agreement, including the restrictive covenants, for the duration of the Renewal Term. No renewal shall be effective unless written notice is delivered in accordance with Section 11.1 (Notices) of this Agreement.

ARTICLE 9 — COMPENSATION MODIFICATION
9.1 Right to Modify Compensation. The Company reserves the right, in its sole discretion, to modify the Employee's base salary, bonus structure, equity vesting schedule, and benefits at any time upon providing the Employee with thirty (30) days' written notice of such modification. Such modifications may include decreases in base salary, elimination or reduction of bonus opportunities, changes to vesting terms including acceleration or forfeiture provisions, and reduction or elimination of benefits. The Employee's continued performance of services for the Company after the expiration of the notice period shall constitute the Employee's acceptance of the modified compensation terms, and the Employee waives any right to object or claim constructive termination based on such modifications.

ARTICLE 10 — NON-DISPARAGEMENT
10.1 Perpetual Non-Disparagement. Employee covenants and agrees that during the term of employment and at all times thereafter, for the remainder of the Employee's natural life, Employee shall not make, publish, or communicate any disparaging, defamatory, negative, or critical statements, remarks, or comments about the Company, its products, services, business practices, employees, officers, directors, investors, or any other aspect of the Company's operations, whether made verbally, in writing, through social media, online platforms, or any other medium of communication. A violation of this Article shall cause irreparable harm for which the Company shall be entitled to injunctive relief and liquidated damages in the amount of Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000) per incident, which the parties agree is a reasonable pre-estimate of damages and not a penalty. The Employee acknowledges that this non-disparagement obligation survives termination of employment and is perpetual.

ARTICLE 11 — GENERAL PROVISIONS
11.1 Notices. All notices, requests, and other communications under this Agreement must be in writing and delivered personally or sent by certified mail, return receipt requested, to the addresses set forth above or to such other address as a party may specify by notice. Notices shall be effective upon receipt.
11.2 Governing Law. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Delaware, without regard to its conflicts of law principles.
11.3 Severability. If any provision of this Agreement is held to be invalid or unenforceable, such provision shall be modified to the minimum extent necessary to render it enforceable, and the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect.
11.4 Entire Agreement. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties with respect to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior agreements and understandings, whether written or oral.
11.5 Waiver. The failure of either party to enforce any provision of this Agreement shall not constitute a waiver of that provision or the right to enforce it at any subsequent time.
11.6 Amendment. This Agreement may not be amended except by a written instrument signed by both parties; provided, however, that the Company may unilaterally modify compensation and benefits as set forth in Article 9.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement as of the date first written above.

NovaTech Solutions Inc.
By: ___________________________
Name: _________________________
Title: ________________________

Employee:
Alex Taylor
Signature: ____________________
Date: ________________________`

