                defense: "The renewal term provides stability for both parties and ensures that the Company can plan projects and resource allocation. The Employee accepted this clause and had ample time to provide notice; failing to do so is a consequence of their own inaction.",
                verdict: "LexGuard recommends negotiating the notice period down to 30 days and adding language that the non-renewal does not alter the at-will nature of employment, so that the employee can still resign at any time. The clause as written turns a job into a trap."
